On Wed, 3 Aug 2005, Will Anderson wrote:
snipped for the list police!> 
> 
> I'm not disagreeing with dave, just to add a little 
info to this post on 2bbl applications, in my limited 
experience--most 2bbl carbs out there that I have 
seen are progressive (open first primary barrel then secondary),
 however these WON'T work with what dave calls the 
"correct" manifold (secondary feeding 2 cyls and primary feeding 2 cyls).

> 
> The 2100 shown (I'm assuming this is similar to or same thing as bugspray?) 
has synchronous barrels (i.e. not progressive) that open at the same 
time, and dave's advice on manifolds applies to these primarily. 
> 
> somewhere I even saw a kit to run dual progressives. 
why one would want to run such a frankenstein instead of DRLAs or IDFs I dunno. 
> 
> I have a DP manifold (big plenum, barrels oriented longitudinally to the bus) 
similar to the "not a bugspray" manifold example that I would be happy to sell 
to you Denny, PM me for more info, heat riser tubes are virtually new.
> 
> As with any carb, the key is going to be running the proper idle, 
main and air correction jets once you have it properly fitted.
